data.description: Experience true Southern living in this gorgeous 1925 farm home, surrounded by majestic live oaks, a century-old magnolia tree, & azaleas on 2 acres along a countryside road. Relax on the front porch in the evenings & listen to the soothing melodies of nature. This spacious home has original character at every turn. Explore the attic to discover the preserved original beadboard ceilings ready to be revealed if you desire. This well-maintained property includes a main home with 4 br & 2.5 ba, a sparkling in-ground pool complete with pool bar & a full bath, a 2-car garage with a small separate workshop, and a spacious shop at the rear of the property spanning 1,840 sq ft with 1 bay door.  The Main Home Upon entering from the wide front porch, notice the low-maintenance exterior of vinyl siding and columns. From your front porch, you have a view of a farm field and nature... no neighbors in site. Inside, the original solid wood door leads you to the expansive living room with 12-foot ceilings, oak hardwood floors, a gas log fireplace, and a beautiful crystal chandelier. To the left, another room with 12' ceilings can serve as a formal dining area or versatile space. Through the French doors is the huge kitchen area, featuring a dining space, seating area, gas fireplace, built-ins, and tiled flooring. The kitchen is equipped with custom pull-out shelving in the pantry, a stacked wall oven and microwave, an electric cooktop with a Griddle option, a new dishwasher, and abundant cabinet storage. The unique butcher block island has a rich history, originating from Olanta Middle School in the 1950s where one of the children who grew up in the home was principal for 40 years. Down the hallway, discover four bedrooms and two full baths. One bedroom provides access to the charming "Cypress Room", a sunroom with cypress-clad walls and tile flooring leading to the fully fenced backyard. Be sure to explore the attic, a remarkable space for storage displaying the home's history with original beadboard ceilings showcasing writings from the original owner's children about farm life and The Beatles. The home also includes a propane-powered whole-home generator.  Two Car Garage The two-car garage features electrically operated doors and includes an additional  room ideal for use as a potting shed or a compact tool shed.
